        <section eId="sec_17a_597">
          <num>17a-597</num>
          <heading>(Formerly Sec. 17-257r). Appeal of board orders and decisions</heading>
          <subsection eId="17a_597__subsec_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Any order of the board entered pursuant to subdivision</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="17a_597__subsec_a__subsec_2">
              <num>(2)</num>
              <content>
                <p>or</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="17a_597__subsec_a__subsec_3">
              <num>(3)</num>
              <content>
                <p>of section17a-584or pursuant to section17a-587may be appealed to the Superior Court pursuant to section4-183. The board shall give notice of the right to judicial review to the acquittee, counsel for the acquittee and the state's attorney.</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="17a_597__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A decision by the board that the acquittee is a person who should be discharged made pursuant to subdivision</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="17a_597__subsec_b__subsec_1">
              <num>(1)</num>
              <content>
                <p>of section17a-584, section17a-592or subsection</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="17a_597__subsec_d">
            <num>(d)</num>
            <content>
              <p>of section17a-593shall not be subject to judicial review pursuant to section4-183.
